The National Universities Commission (NUC) has directed all universities across the county to resume academic activities on Monday, January 18, 2021. in line with a directive issued on Friday by . The NUC, in a directive issued to the tertiary institutions on Friday, said the directive comes from the advice of the Presidential Task Force (PTF) on COVID-19 on the resumption of schools. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCEÂ DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! The Deputy Executive Secretary (Administration) of the commission, Mr. Chris Maiyaki, in a statement in Abuja, urged the universities to safeguard lives by strictly adhering to the extant safety protocols and the guidelines of the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) on COVID-19. He noted that the guidelines have been communicated on several occasions to university authorities through circulars from the commission. Kilishi: Onuesoke Calls For Scrapping Of RMRDC Over 30-Year Non-Performance BREAKING: Court Dismisses Certificate Forgery Case Against Gov Obaseki The Deputy Executive Secretary stated that on the resumption of academic activities, universities must under no circumstance violate the full cycle of the semester system, consistent with the Benchmark Minimum Academic Standards (BMAS) approved by the NUC, as well as other extant quality assurance standards and guidelines. He, however, said officers on Grade Level 12 and below should remain at home for a five-week period as earlier directed by the federal government. Public universities in the country have been closed since March 2020 after the Academic Staff Union of Universities (ASUU) embarked on an indefinite strike that lasted about 10 months. A lockdown imposed by the government to contain the spread of COVID-19 also forced the students to remain at home.